Logical Function Objects
    Note
    The allTrue() and anyTrue() functions are just given as examples. 
    In fact, the Standard Library provides the std::all_of() and any_of() algorithms 
    that perform the same operations, but that have the benefit of short-circuiting, 
    so they are more performant.

